utils = require "Utilities"
local min = Component.GetProperty("minValue") local max = Component.GetProperty("maxValue") local width = Component.Call("Height") - Component.Call("handle.Height") local scale = 1 local prev_value = min - 1
function Reset() min = Component.GetProperty("minValue") max = Component.GetProperty("maxValue") if max - min > 0 then scale = width / (max - min) else scale = 0 end
Component.Call("handle.LuaCall", "Reset") end
function InitState() Update() end
function ValueSet( value )
Component.SetProperty( "Value", utils.RoundToInt( value ) ) Update() end
function ValueGet()
return utils.RoundToInt(Component.GetProperty("Value"))
end
function Update()
local value = utils.RoundToInt(Component.GetProperty("Value"))
if (value < min) then value = min else if (value > max) then value = max end end Component.SetProperty("Value", value)
handleX, handleY = Component.Call("handle.Position") ourX, ourY = Component.Call("Position")
handleY = utils.RoundToInt(scale * value)
Component.Call("handle.MoveTo", handleX, ourY + handleY)
if prev_value ~= value then prev_value = value notify = Component.GetProperty("Notify") if notify ~= nil then Component.CallByAddress(notify, "LuaCall", "Notify", Address, value) end end
--[[ local value = Component.GetProperty("Value") if (value < min) then value = min else if (value > max) then value = max end end Component.SetProperty("Value", value)
handleX, handleY = Component.Call("handle.Position") ourX, ourY = Component.Call("Position")
handleY = scale * value
Component.Call("handle.MoveTo", handleX, ourY + handleY)
out.shane( "Updating VSlider: Prev value "..prev_value..", New value "..value )
if prev_value ~= value then prev_value = value notify = Component.GetProperty("Notify") if notify ~= nil then
out.shane( "Notifying" ) Component.CallByAddress(notify, "LuaCall", "Notify")
end end --]]
end
function Layout(children) Update() end

uientry.unicode: This column shows the current status of each game. || By mousing over the icons in this column you can see if the game is available for you to join or if there is something preventing you.

This column enables players to search for games by title. || You can sort this list alphabetically by clicking on the column title. || Sometimes the host will have specific rules, such as beginners only or no cavalry units, and will mention this in the game title. || You can search for preferences like these in the search dialog in the top right-hand corner.

Each battle uses a map template for its location. || You can sort this list by clicking on the column title. || This will help you to find your favourite location for engagements, be it an arid desert or humid jungle.

This shows how many players have joined this battle and how many more are needed. || You can sort this list by clicking on the column title. || This is helpful if you are looking to fight a one-on-one battle rather than several players, or vice versa.
This displays the games' current connection status. || You can sort these by clicking on the column title.

This displays the funds available to each player for recruiting their force. || You can sort this list by clicking on the title. || Larger funds mean larger forces, so use this column to find a battle size to your liking.

This shows the battle type, be it land, sea, or siege. || You can sort this list by clicking on the column title. || Each type of battle has its own distinct gameplay and features. || Find a favourite type here, or perhaps try something new.

This is the host of the game. || They are responsible for the details of the battle, including any specific rules, and who can and can't join. || Their ranking is displayed their skill rating column. || You may wish to play with a host with a similar ranking to yourself, or challenge yourself with someone of a higher rank.

This is the host's ranking. || You can sort this list by clicking on the column title. || You may wish to play with a host with a similar ranking to yourself, or challenge yourself with someone of a higher rank.

state.unicode: Closed || This game is not available for you to join. || It is already full and requires a password.
Closed || This game is not available for you to join. || It is already full and may have started.
Open || This game is open to you and available to join.
Password required || You can join this game is you have the correct password.

function OnSelect() local txt = textfield:LuaCall("Value") parent:LuaCall("SearchForGame", txt) end

uientry.unicode: When hosting, you can set location, size, and type of battle. || If you wish, you can establish rules with the other players, such as not using any cavalry units or an artillery only battle! || You can allow any players to join, or set a password so it is only open to friends.
This allows you to watch a multiplayer battle.
This will take you out of multiplayer mode to the single player battle menu. || Use the single player menu to practice against AI opponents before returning here to take on other players.
Whenever you play a battle, you get the option to save it as a replay. || Watch your greatest victories and worst defeats here.

Check this box for a ranked battle. || If a battle is ranked, the victor of the battle is awarded skill points. || This contributes to your command stars. || Command stars denote ranking, and each player's ranking affects how many skill points can be won. || For example, winning a battle against a higher ranking player than yourself will gain you more skill points than playing against someone closer to your ranking.
Check this box for a friendly battle. || Friendly battles are not ranked and will not earn the victor skill points. || For skill points you will need to win a ranked battle.
Check this box for a friendly battle. || Friendly battles are not ranked and will not earn the victor skill points. || For skill points you will need to win a ranked battle.
